## Why This Matters for Orchestrators

As you mentioned, tools like **Docker Swarm** and **Kubernetes** (which uses "Liveness and Readiness Probes") rely heavily on this.

If a container turns `unhealthy`, Docker Swarm will automatically destroy that container and spin up a fresh one in its place. It will also stop routing user traffic to that specific container until it passes its health checks again, ensuring your users never hit a broken page.
